NEWCASTLE DISEASE, PIGEONS - BELGIUM
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Newcastle disease - Europe 980324230828
Date: Fri, 7 Aug 1998 18:04:05 -0500
Source: OIE disease information
Via: Martin Hugh-Jones <mehj2020@vt8200.vetmed.lsu.edu>

See also: 24 October 1997, 4 July 1997
(Date of last previously reported outbreak: October 1998).[sic
Emergency report
Translation of a fax received on 6 August 1998 from Dr L. Hallet,
Counsellor General,
Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Brussels:
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 5 June 1998.
Location: Sint-Genesius-Rode district, Flemish Brabant
No. of outbreaks: 1
Description of affected population: hobby flock of pigeons.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible: 52
cases: ...
deaths: 30
destroyed: 0
slaughtered: 0
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: CERVA-CODA, Brussels.
B. Diagnostic tests used: immunofluorescence, virus isolation, monoclonal
antibodies, virus culture in embryonated eggs.
C. Causal agent: velogenic strain of Newcastle disease virus.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: unknown.
B. Other epidemiological details: no further deaths after symptomatic
treatment.
Control measures during reporting period: voluntary diagnostic testing;
establishment placed under quarantine.
--
